  "description": "Sulfuric acid (lead chamber process 65-70%, contact process 96-98%), nitric acid (from nitrates + H₂SO₄, later Ostwald process), hydrochloric acid (NaCl + H₂SO₄ or direct H₂ + Cl₂ synthesis), and hydrofluoric acid (CaF₂ + H₂SO₄, extremely hazardous). HF is uniquely dangerous and essential for glass and silicon etching.",
